name: Titanium.App.iOS.SearchableItemAttributeSet
summary: The SearchableItemAttributeSet module defines metadata properties for SearchItem and UserActivity objects.

properties.name: addedDate
properties.summary: The date that the item was moved into the current location.
properties.description: The date will be a string in the following format: "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSS'+0000'" For example, 2015-12-25T23:30:55.978+0000

properties.name: album
properties.summary: The title for a collection of media.

properties.name: alternateNames
properties.summary: An array of localized strings of alternate display names for this item.

properties.name: artist
properties.summary: The artist for the media.

properties.name: audiences
properties.summary: A class of entity for whom the resource is intended or useful.
properties.description: A class of entity may be determined by the creator, publisher or third party.

properties.name: audioBitRate
properties.summary: The audio bit rate.

properties.name: audioChannelCount
properties.summary: The number of channels in the audio data contained in the file.
properties.description: This item only represents the number of discreet channels of audio data found in the file. It does not indicate any configuration of the data in regards to a user's speaker setup.

properties.name: audioEncodingApplication
properties.summary: The name of the application that encoded the data contained in the audio file.

properties.name: audioSampleRate
properties.summary: The sample rate of the audio data contained in the file.
properties.description: The sample rate is a float value representing Hertz (audio_frames/second), for example, 44100.0 or 22254.54.

properties.name: audioTrackNumber
properties.summary: The track number of a song/composition when it is part of an album.

properties.name: codecs
properties.summary: The codecs used to encode/decode the media.

properties.name: comment
properties.summary: Comment related to a file.

properties.name: composer
properties.summary: The composer of the song/composition contained in the audio file.

properties.name: contactKeywords
properties.summary: A list of contacts that are somehow associated with this document beyond what is captured as Author.

properties.name: containerDisplayName
properties.summary: Display of the search container

properties.name: containerIdentifier
properties.summary: Identifier for the search container

properties.name: containerOrder
properties.summary: Order the search container is displayed.

properties.name: containerTitle
properties.summary: Title displayed in the search container

properties.name: contentCreationDate
properties.summary: The date that the contents of the item were created.
properties.description: The date will be a string in the following format: "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSS'+0000'" For example, 2015-12-25T23:30:55.978+0000

properties.name: contentDescription
properties.summary: An account of the content of the resource.
properties.description: Description may include but is not limited to: an abstract, table of contents, reference to a graphical representation of content or a free-text account of the content.

properties.name: contentModificationDate
properties.summary: The date that the contents of the item were last modified.
properties.description: The date will be a string in the following format: "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSS'+0000'" For example, 2015-12-25T23:30:55.978+0000

properties.name: contentRating
properties.summary: Whether or not the item has explicit content. Set to 1 for explicit or 0 for clean.

properties.name: contentSources
properties.summary: Used to indicate where the item was obtained from.

properties.name: contentType
properties.summary: UTI Type pedigree for an item.

properties.name: contentTypeTree
properties.summary: Array of strings related to the content tree of the item.

properties.name: contentURL
properties.summary: File URL representing the content to be indexed.

properties.name: contributors
properties.summary: Used to designate the entity responsible for making contributions to the content of the resource.

properties.name: copyright
properties.summary: Copyright of the content.

properties.name: coverage
properties.summary: Used to designate the extent or scope of the content of the resource.

properties.name: creator
properties.summary: Application used to create the document content (e.g. "Word","Framemaker", etc.).

properties.name: deliveryType
properties.summary: The delivery type of the item. Set to 0 for fast start and 1 for RTSP.

properties.name: director
properties.summary: Director of the item, for example, the movie director.

properties.name: displayName
properties.summary: A localized string to be displayed in the UI for this item.

properties.name: downloadedDate
properties.summary: The date that the file was last downloaded / received.
properties.description: The date will be a string in the following format: "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSS'+0000'" For example, 2015-12-25T23:30:55.978+0000

properties.name: duration
properties.summary: Duration in seconds of the content of the item (if appropriate).

properties.name: editors
properties.summary: The list of editor/editors that have worked on this item.

properties.name: encodingApplications
properties.summary: Software used to convert the original content into a PDF stream.

properties.name: fileSize
properties.summary: Size of the document in MB.

properties.name: fontNames
properties.summary: Array of font names used in the item.

properties.name: fullyFormattedAddress
properties.summary: The fully formatted address of the item (obtained from MapKit).

properties.name: generalMIDISequence
properties.summary: Used to indicates whether the MIDI sequence contained in the file is setup for use with a General MIDI device.
properties.description: Should be 1 if true and 0 otherwise.

properties.name: genre
properties.summary: Genre of the item, for example, movie genre.

properties.name: identifier
properties.summary: Used to reference to the resource within a given context.
properties.description: Recommended best practice is to identify the resource by means of a string or number conforming to a formal identification system.

properties.name: information
properties.summary: Information about the item.

properties.name: itemContentType
properties.summary: Content type of the attribute set.
properties.description: Must be set to create a SearchableItemAttributeSet object. Set to an identifier in the iOS Developer Library: System-Declared Uniform Type Identifiers

properties.name: keySignature
properties.summary: The musical key of the song/composition contained in an audio file.

properties.name: keywords
properties.summary: Represents keywords associated with this particular item. Example keywords might be Birthday etc.

properties.name: kind
properties.summary: Kind that the item represents.

properties.name: languages
properties.summary: Used to designate the languages of the intellectual content of the resource.

properties.name: lastUsedDate
properties.summary: The date that the item was last used.
properties.description: The date will be a string in the following format: "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSS'+0000'" For example, 2015-12-25T23:30:55.978+0000

properties.name: local
properties.summary: Whether or not the item is local. Set to 1 if true and 0 otherwise.

properties.name: lyricist
properties.summary: The lyricist/text writer for song/composition contained in the audio file.

properties.name: mediaTypes
properties.summary: Media types present in the content.

properties.name: metadataModificationDate
properties.summary: The date that the last metadata attribute was changed.
properties.description: The date will be a string in the following format: "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSS'+0000'" For example, 2015-12-25T23:30:55.978+0000

properties.name: musicalGenre
properties.summary: The musical genre of the song/composition contained in the audio file.

properties.name: musicalInstrumentCategory
properties.summary: Metadata attribute that stores the category of instrument.
properties.description: Files should have an instrument associated with them ("Other Instrument" is provided as a catch-all). For some categories, like "Keyboards" there are instrument names which provide a more detailed instrument definition, for example, Piano, Organ, etc.

properties.name: musicalInstrumentName
properties.summary: Metadata attribute that stores the name of instrument.
properties.description: Relative to the instrument category. Files can have an instrument name associated with them if they have certain instrument categories, for example, the category Percussion has multiple instruments, including Conga and Bongo.

properties.name: organizations
properties.summary: Used to indicate company/Organization that created the document.

properties.name: originalFormat
properties.summary: Original format of the movie.

properties.name: originalSource
properties.summary: Original source of the movie.

properties.name: pageCount
properties.summary: Number of pages in the item.

properties.name: pageHeight
properties.summary: Height in points (72 points per inch) of the document page.
properties.description: First page only for PDF's - other pages within the PDF may not be the same height.

properties.name: pageWidth
properties.summary: Width in points (72 points per inch) of the document page.
properties.description: First page only for PDF's - other pages within the PDF may not be the same width.

properties.name: participants
properties.summary: The list of people who are visible in an image or movie or written about in a document.

properties.name: path
properties.summary: The complete path to the item.

properties.name: performers
properties.summary: Performers in the movie.

properties.name: playCount
properties.summary: User play count of this item.

properties.name: postalCode
properties.summary: The postal code for the item according to guidelines established by the provider.

properties.name: producer
properties.summary: Producer of the content.

properties.name: projects
properties.summary: The list of projects that this item is part of.

properties.name: publishers
properties.summary: Used to designate the entity responsible for making the resource available.

properties.name: rating
properties.summary: User rating of this item out of 5 stars.

properties.name: ratingDescription
properties.summary: A description of the rating, for example, the number of reviewers.

properties.name: recordingDate
properties.summary: The recording date of the song/composition.
properties.description:
This information differs from the contentCreationDate attribute as it indicates the date that the 'art' was created, in contrast to contentCreationDate which for example, could indicate the creation date of an edited or 'mastered' version of the original art.

The date will be a string in the following format: "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSS'+0000'" For example, 2015-12-25T23:30:55.978+0000

properties.name: relatedUniqueIdentifier
properties.summary: For activities this is the unique identifier for the item this activity is related to.

properties.name: rights
properties.summary: Used to provide a link to information about rights held in and over resource.

properties.name: role
properties.summary: Used to indicate the role of the document creator.

properties.name: securityMethod
properties.summary: Security (encryption) method used in the file.

properties.name: streamable
properties.summary: Whether the content is prepared for streaming. Set to 0 for not streamable and 1 for streamable.

properties.name: subject
properties.summary: Subject of the the item.

properties.name: subThoroughfare
properties.summary: The sub-location (e.g., street number) for the item according to guidelines established by the provider.

properties.name: supportsNavigation
properties.summary: Used to determine if navigation is supported.
properties.description: If supportsNavigation is set to 1, and the item has the latitude and longitude properties set, then the latitude and longitude may be used for navigation. For example, supportsNavigation would be set on a restaurant review, but not on a photo.

properties.name: supportsPhoneCall
properties.summary: Used to indicate that using the phone number is appropriate.
properties.description: If supportsPhoneCall is 1 and the item has the phoneNumbers property set, then the phone number may be used to initiate phone calls. This should be used to indicate that using the phone number is appropriate, and a primary action for the user. For example, supportsPhoneCall would be set on a business, but not an academic paper that happens to have phone numbers for the authors or the institution.

properties.name: tempo
properties.summary: The tempo of the music contained in the audio file in Beats Per Minute.

properties.name: theme
properties.summary: Theme of the the item.

properties.name: thoroughfare
properties.summary: The location (e.g., street name) for the item according to guidelines established by the provider.

properties.name: thumbnailData
properties.summary: Image data for thumbnail for this item.

properties.name: thumbnailURL
properties.summary: File URL pointing to a thumbnail image for this item.

properties.name: timeSignature
properties.summary: The time signature of the musical composition contained in the audio/MIDI file.

properties.name: title
properties.summary: The title of the particular item.

properties.name: totalBitRate
properties.summary: The total bit rate (audio and video combined) of the media.

properties.name: url
properties.summary: URL of the item.

properties.name: version
properties.summary: A version specifier for this item.

properties.name: videoBitRate
properties.summary: The video bit rate.
